TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chapman, David A
AU  - Gallmeyer, Michael F
AU  - Martin, J Spencer
T1  - Aggregate Tail Risk and Expected Returns
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/ray002
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
SP  - 36
EP  - 76
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Do stocks bear a crash risk premium? We examine the empirical performance of the tail index measure from Kelly and Jiang (2014). We find that the tail index explains the cross-section of the discount rate component of returns, but not the cash-flow component. Moreover, in the time series the tail index is uncorrelated with theoretically motivated measures of aggregate uncertainty and systemic risk. In contrast, the tail index Granger causes and is Granger caused by the level of the term structure, and the slope of the term structure Granger causes tail risk.Received June 22, 2016; editorial decision December 23, 2017 by Editor Raman Uppal.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/ray002
ER  - 



