TY  - JOUR
AU  - Qian, Hong
AU  - Zhong, Zhaodong (Ken)
T1  - Do Hedge Funds Possess Private Information about IPO Stocks? Evidence from Post-IPO Holdings*
PY  - 2018
Y1  - 2018/06/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/rax018
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
SP  - 117
EP  - 152
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Using hedge funds’ holdings of IPO stocks, we find that stocks with abnormally high hedge fund holdings, based on stock and deal characteristics, yield abnormal returns. Moreover, hedge funds are able to sell IPO stocks in a timely fashion before long-run underperforming periods start, suggesting that hedge funds possess information advantages in IPO stocks. Finally, we address the question of where hedge funds may have obtained their information advantages. Hedge funds earn higher abnormal returns in “connected” stocks when their prime brokers also serve as IPO underwriters, indicating that such connections enable hedge funds to make more informed investment decisions in IPO stocks.Received December 31, 2014; editorial decision May 27, 2017 by Editor Wayne Ferson.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/rax018
ER  - 



